    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="245">
      <subfield code="a">Suppression of Trapped Energetic Ions Driven Resistive Interchange Modes with Electron Cyclotron Heating in a Helical Plasma</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="260">
      <subfield code="c">2017-03-20</subfield>
      <subfield code="t">published</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="300">
      <subfield code="a">5</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="520">
      <subfield code="a">The resistive interchange mode destabilized by the resonant interaction with the trapped energetic ions is fully suppressed when the injected power of electron cyclotron heating exceeds a certain threshold. It is shown for the first time that the complete stabilization of the energetic-particle-driven mode without relaxing the energetic particle (EP) pressure gradient is possible by reducing the radial width of the eigenmodes δw, especially when δw narrows to a small enough value relative to the finite orbit width of EP.</subfield>
      <subfield code="9">APS</subfield>
    </datafield>
